Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of collisions in a random urn occupancy model, which is a classic problem in discrete mathematics. The use of weighted context-free grammars and the generation of combinatorial objects suggest a connection to formal language theory (cs.FL). The analysis of the coverage and redundancy of sets of generated objects is related to the study of random graphs and hypergraphs, which falls under the scope of computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). The use of asymptotic estimates and polynomially computable exact forms is a common technique in algorithm analysis and data structures (cs.DS). Overall, the paper seems to fit well within the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category.
